#. type: Title #
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-composite.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "`Composite` - grouping multiple validation rules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-composite.md
msgid ""
"`Composite` allows to group multiple rules and configure the common "
"[skipping options](conditional-validation.md), such as `skipOnEmpty`, "
"`skipOnError` and `when`, for the whole set only once instead of repeating "
"them in each rule:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-composite.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Composite;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Email;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Length;\n"
"\n"
"new Composite(\n"
"    [\n"
"        new Length(max: 255),\n"
"        new Email(),\n"
"    ],\n"
"    skipOnEmpty: true,\n"
");\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-composite.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reusing multiple rules / single rule with the same options"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-composite.md
msgid ""
"`Composite` is one of the few built-in rules that is not `final`. This means "
"that you can extend it and override the `getRules()` method to create a "
"reusable set of rules:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-composite.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Composite;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Length;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Regex;\n"
"\n"
"final class UsernameRuleSet extends Composite\n"
"{\n"
"    public function getRules(): array\n"
"    {\n"
"        return [\n"
"            new Length(min: 2, max: 20),\n"
"            new Regex('~^[a-z_\\-]*$~i'),\n"
"        ];\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-composite.md
msgid "And use it just like a single regular rule:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-composite.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Validator;\n"
"\n"
"$result = (new Validator())->validate('John', new UsernameRuleSet());\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-composite.md
msgid ""
"It can also be combined with [Nested](built-in-rules-nested.md) rule to "
"reuse rules for multiple properties:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-composite.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Composite;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Nested;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Number;\n"
"\n"
"final class CoordinatesRuleSet extends Composite\n"
"{\n"
"    public function getRules(): array\n"
"    {\n"
"        return [\n"
"            new Nested(\n"
"                'latitude' => new Number(min: -90, max: 90),\n"
"                'longitude' => new Number(min: -90, max: 90),\n"
"            ),\n"
"        ];\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-composite.md
msgid ""
"Even the problem of reusing only one rule with the same arguments can be "
"solved with `Composite`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-composite.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Composite;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Number;\n"
"\n"
"final class ChartCoordinateRuleSet extends Composite\n"
"{\n"
"    public function getRules(): array\n"
"    {\n"
"        return [new Number(min: -10, max: 10)];\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
